Q10. Use ggplot, make a plot with weights vs heights of the players, color by Teams. Give it an appropriate title.

In all scientific literature, a graph is always referred as Y against X (y vs x). Make sure you put “weights” on y as requested here.

loadPkg("ggplot2")
ggplot(data=baseball)+
  geom_point(mapping = aes(x=height, y=weight, color=Team))+
  ggtitle("Scatter plot of baseball player weigth(y) vs height(x)")
